    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;An extension to Transport Layer Security (TLS) is defined that allows endpoints to negotiate the maximum size of protected records that each will send the other.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This replaces the maximum fragment length extension defined in RFC 6066.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
